This topic describes how to access logs and metrics for component VMs and app containers on your Pivotal Platform deployment. It includes information about the available logs and metrics for the Pivotal Application Service (PAS) and Pivotal Container Service (PKS) runtimes.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

There are different methods for accessing logs and metrics for VMs and app containers on Pivotal Platform depending on if you use the PAS or PKS app runtime for your deployment. 

There are also different permissions required to access logs and metrics on PAS and PKS.

You can use the sections in this topic to understand how to access logs and metrics on your PAS or PKS deployment based on your user role permissions.

## <a id="vm-logs"></a> View VM Logs

This section describes how users on Pivotal Platform can view logs for Pivotal Platform VMs. 

Pivotal Platform emits logs for all VMs, including VMs for runtime component VMs and service tile VMs.

### <a id="vm-logs-pas"></a> View VM Logs on PAS

Pivotal Platform emits logs for VMs as Syslog RFC 5424. See [RFC 5424 - The Syslog Protocol](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424) in the Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) documentation.

To view logs for Pivotal Platform VMs, configure a platform-level syslog drain in each runtime and service tile for which you want logs.

For more information, see the documentation for the runtime or service tile. 


